79.9	Bodhi	Bodhi	Bodhi (Sanskrit: बोधि) is both a Pāli and Sanskrit word traditionally translated into English with the word "enlightenment", but which means awakened. In Buddhism it is the knowledge possessed by a Buddha into the nature of things . The word "buddha" means "awakened one." Although its most common usage is in the context of Buddhism, bodhi is also present as a concept in other Indian philosophies and traditions.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/df/Dharma_Wheel.svg/100px-Dharma_Wheel.svg.png
